---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Custom CRM Development for Small Business | OpsHQ Digital"
  description="Stop losing leads to spreadsheets. Custom CRM with automated follow-ups, payment tracking & daily digests. Seattle-based developer."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-navy-950 text-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16 md:py-24">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <!-- Text side -->
        <div>
          <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold leading-tight mb-6">Stop Losing Leads to Spreadsheets and Missed Follow-Ups</h1>
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-300 mb-8">Your leads deserve better than a spreadsheet. And so do you.</p>
          <a href="/contact/?service=crm" class="inline-flex items-center px-8 py-4 bg-blue-500 text-white font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-600 transition-colors text-lg">
            Request a Free Discovery Call →
          </a>
        </div>
        <!-- Image side -->
        <div class="relative">
          <img src="/images/hero-crm.jpg" alt="Custom CRM dashboard with lead tracking pipeline and automated follow-up system" class="rounded-2xl shadow-2xl shadow-blue-500/10 w-full" />
          <div class="absolute -inset-1 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-500/20 to-teal-500/20 rounded-2xl blur-xl -z-10"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Problem -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
        <div class="w-2 h-2 bg-blue-500 rounded-full"></div>
        <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-500 uppercase tracking-wider">The Problem</span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-navy-950 mb-6">You Know the Feeling</h2>
      <div class="prose text-slate-600 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
        <p>A customer emails on Monday. You mean to follow up Tuesday. By Thursday, they've booked with your competitor.</p>
        <p>It's not that you don't care — it's that you're running your entire business from a tangle of spreadsheets, email threads, and sticky notes. You can't see which leads need attention, which deposits are outstanding, or which customers are about to slip away.</p>
        <p>Off-the-shelf CRMs like Salesforce or HubSpot cost $50-150/user/month and force you to work their way. You end up paying for features you don't use and missing the ones you need.</p>
        <p class="font-medium text-navy-950">What if your CRM actually matched how you sell?</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Solution -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-slate-50">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-2 mb-4">
        <div class="w-2 h-2 bg-blue-500 rounded-full"></div>
        <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-500 uppercase tracking-wider">The Solution</span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-navy-950 mb-12 text-center">A CRM That Works the Way You Do</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200">
          <div class="text-2xl mb-3">📋</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-navy-950 mb-2">Custom Lead Tracking</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Pipeline stages that match YOUR actual sales process. Every lead gets tracked from first inquiry through completed job — nothing falls through the cracks.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200">
          <div class="text-2xl mb-3">📧</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-navy-950 mb-2">Morning Briefing Email</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">One email at the start of every day with exactly what you need: which leads need attention, what's coming up, and where money is outstanding.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200">
          <div class="text-2xl mb-3">💳</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-navy-950 mb-2">Payment Tracking</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Integrated payment processing with deposit tracking, payment link generation, and automatic reconciliation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200">
          <div class="text-2xl mb-3">🔄</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-navy-950 mb-2">Real-Time Sync</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Bi-directional sync with your email, calendar, and existing tools. When a customer emails, the CRM updates automatically.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200">
          <div class="text-2xl mb-3">🤖</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-navy-950 mb-2">AI-Powered Follow-Up</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Intelligent email drafts that match your brand voice. The system drafts responses that sound like you at your best.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200">
          <div class="text-2xl mb-3">📊</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-navy-950 mb-2">Lead Health Scoring</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Automatic scoring based on responsiveness, timeline, and engagement. Red/yellow/green at a glance.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Results -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-2 mb-4">
        <div class="w-2 h-2 bg-blue-500 rounded-full"></div>
        <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-500 uppercase tracking-wider">Results</span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-navy-950 mb-8 text-center">Results That Speak for Themselves</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-6 mb-8">
        <div class="bg-slate-100 rounded-lg p-6 text-center">
          <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-blue-500">48h → 5min</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-2">Response time</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-slate-100 rounded-lg p-6 text-center">
          <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-blue-500">200+</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-2">Leads managed</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-slate-100 rounded-lg p-6 text-center">
          <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-blue-500">15+ hrs</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-2">Saved per week</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-slate-100 rounded-lg p-6 text-center">
          <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-blue-500">99%+</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-2">Uptime</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-center">
        <a href="/work/transportation-crm/" class="text-blue-500 font-medium hover:text-blue-600 transition-colors">Read the full case study →</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-slate-50">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
        <div class="w-2 h-2 bg-blue-500 rounded-full"></div>
        <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-500 uppercase tracking-wider">FAQ</span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-navy-950 mb-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <details class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200 group" open>
          <summary class="text-lg font-semibold text-navy-950 cursor-pointer list-none flex justify-between items-center">
            How is this different from Salesforce or HubSpot?
            <span class="text-slate-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▼</span>
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Those are general-purpose platforms that force you into their workflow. We build your CRM around how you actually sell — your pipeline stages, your follow-up cadence, your pricing. And you're not paying $50-150/user/month forever.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200 group">
          <summary class="text-lg font-semibold text-navy-950 cursor-pointer list-none flex justify-between items-center">
            How long does it take to build a custom CRM?
            <span class="text-slate-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▼</span>
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Most CRM projects take 4-8 weeks from kickoff to launch. You'll see working software within the first 2-3 weeks.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200 group">
          <summary class="text-lg font-semibold text-navy-950 cursor-pointer list-none flex justify-between items-center">
            What if I already have customer data in spreadsheets?
            <span class="text-slate-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▼</span>
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">We'll migrate it. Part of every project is getting your existing data into the new system cleanly.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200 group">
          <summary class="text-lg font-semibold text-navy-950 cursor-pointer list-none flex justify-between items-center">
            Do I need to be technical to use it?
            <span class="text-slate-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform">▼</span>
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Not at all. If you can read an email and click a button, you can use your CRM. We build for business owners, not engineers.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-navy-950 mb-4">Straightforward Pricing</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 mb-2">Most CRM projects: <span class="font-bold text-navy-950">$5,000 – $25,000</span></p>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mb-8">Monthly maintenance available starting at $500/month. Ongoing platform costs outlined in your proposal.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-navy-950 to-navy-800 text-white py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Let's Build a CRM That Actually Works for You</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-300 mb-8">Every project starts with a free discovery call. No commitment, no sales pitch.</p>
      <a href="/contact/?service=crm" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-4 bg-blue-500 text-white font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-600 transition-colors min-h-[44px] text-lg">
        Request a Discovery Call
      </a>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4 text-sm text-slate-400">
        <a href="/services/ai/" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">AI Automation →</a>
        <a href="/services/web/" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Web Development →</a>
        <a href="/services/cloud/" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Cloud & DevOps →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@graph": [
        {
          "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
          "itemListElement": [
            { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://opshqdigital.com/" },
            { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Services", "item": "https://opshqdigital.com/services/" },
            { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "CRM Development", "item": "https://opshqdigital.com/services/crm/" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "@type": "ProfessionalService",
          "name": "Custom CRM Development — OpsHQ Digital",
          "url": "https://opshqdigital.com/services/crm/",
          "description": "Custom CRM systems with automated follow-ups, payment tracking, and daily digests for small businesses.",
          "provider": { "@id": "https://opshqdigital.com/#organization" },
          "areaServed": { "@type": "City", "name": "Seattle", "addressRegion": "WA" },
          "priceRange": "$5,000 – $25,000"
        },
        {
          "@type": "FAQPage",
          "mainEntity": [
            { "@type": "Question", "name": "How is this different from Salesforce or HubSpot?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Those are general-purpose platforms that force you into their workflow. We build your CRM around how you actually sell — your pipeline stages, your follow-up cadence, your pricing. And you're not paying $50-150/user/month forever." }},
            { "@type": "Question", "name": "How long does it take to build a custom CRM?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Most CRM projects take 4-8 weeks from kickoff to launch. You'll see working software within the first 2-3 weeks." }},
            { "@type": "Question", "name": "What if I already have customer data in spreadsheets?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "We'll migrate it. Part of every project is getting your existing data into the new system cleanly." }},
            { "@type": "Question", "name": "Do I need to be technical to use it?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Not at all. If you can read an email and click a button, you can use your CRM. We build for business owners, not engineers." }}
          ]
        }
      ]
    })} />
  </Fragment>
</BaseLayout>
